  "prompt": "What is the best meme you have or have seen?",
  "response": "Choosing the \"best\" meme is highly subjective and depends on personal taste, cultural context, and timing, but one of the most iconic and enduring memes is **\"Distracted Boyfriend\"**. This meme, featuring a stock photo of a man turning to look at another woman while his girlfriend looks on disapprovingly, has become a universal symbol for temptation, infidelity, and indecision. Its versatility and relatability have made it one of the most widely used and adapted memes across the internet.\n\nOther legendary contenders include:\n- **\"Dogge\" (Doge)**: The Shiba Inu with multicolored Comic Sans text became a cornerstone of meme culture.\n- **\"Pepe the Frog\"**: A once-innocent cartoon frog that evolved into a complex and often controversial meme.\n- **\"Woman Yelling at a Cat\"**: A perfect combination of drama and absurdity, often used to depict arguments or misunderstandings.\n- **\"This is Fine Dog\"**: A dog sitting in a burning room, symbolizing stoicism in the face of chaos.\n\nWhat makes a meme \"the best\" is its ability to resonate, adapt, and stay relevant across different contexts. Which one speaks to you the most? \ud83d\ude04",
